1
00:00:01,550 --> 00:00:02,960
(If you could change the past...)

2
00:00:02,980 --> 00:00:04,740
If I could go back?

3
00:00:07,600 --> 00:00:09,770
I wouldn't want to change the past.

4
00:00:10,440 --> 00:00:13,310
There were mistakes along the way.

5
00:00:13,990 --> 00:00:17,060
But those mistakes were valuable,

6
00:00:17,330 --> 00:00:19,220
they made me who I am today.

7
00:00:20,130 --> 00:00:21,320
All this time,

8
00:00:22,260 --> 00:00:23,900
I've let my mind lead the way.

9
00:00:25,730 --> 00:00:28,950
Every decision had to make sense.

10
00:00:30,680 --> 00:00:31,930
I had to weigh every side.

11
00:00:33,180 --> 00:00:34,760
I'm not even sure

12
00:00:35,080 --> 00:00:36,880
what I'd go back and change

13
00:00:37,330 --> 00:00:38,920
because every day,

14
00:00:39,160 --> 00:00:40,940
I did my very best

15
00:00:41,470 --> 00:00:43,240
as best as a kid could.

16
00:00:44,090 --> 00:00:45,610
I want to thank the past

17
00:00:45,990 --> 00:00:48,300
for teaching me how to love

18
00:00:48,770 --> 00:00:52,130
and care for myself
and those I love.

19
00:00:52,800 --> 00:00:55,400
I choose to focus on what I can do

20
00:00:55,940 --> 00:00:57,000
and do my best

21
00:00:57,600 --> 00:01:00,250
love with all I have, every day.

22
00:01:00,700 --> 00:01:02,070
but if I could go back,

23
00:01:03,440 --> 00:01:05,160
I wouldn't rely on reason alone.

24
00:01:06,920 --> 00:01:08,100
I'd let my feelings

25
00:01:09,700 --> 00:01:12,550
play a part in my decisions

26
00:01:14,310 --> 00:01:17,340
because sometimes I'm sure
I'm right,

27
00:01:18,720 --> 00:01:22,140
yet I feel guilty my whole life.

28
00:01:23,980 --> 00:01:25,560
A pointless question.

29
00:01:26,710 --> 00:01:27,940
The past is gone.

30
00:01:28,539 --> 00:01:30,080
nothing I say can change it.

31
00:01:30,440 --> 00:01:32,210
I don't believe in changing
the past.

32
00:01:32,900 --> 00:01:35,660
but I believe if that day
I'd chosen differently,

33
00:01:36,940 --> 00:01:38,370
today everything would be different.

34
00:01:40,259 --> 00:01:43,270
See you someday.

35
00:01:45,960 --> 00:01:51,700
(Some love just needs
one more chance...)

36
00:03:53,340 --> 00:03:54,340
I'm just not ready yet.

37
00:03:55,079 --> 00:03:56,740
Or maybe you're not sure

38
00:03:58,730 --> 00:04:00,980
you really want me in your life?

39
00:04:03,330 --> 00:04:04,150
I'm sorry.

40
00:04:05,160 --> 00:04:06,510
Maybe I didn't care enough.

41
00:04:07,390 --> 00:04:08,720
But it doesn't mean I felt nothing.

42
00:04:09,250 --> 00:04:12,230
If you felt something for me,
you wouldn't have to hide me.

43
00:04:12,620 --> 00:04:14,510
I'm tired of being hidden.

44
00:04:15,000 --> 00:04:15,870
You should go back.

45
00:04:16,670 --> 00:04:17,850
I left the key card here.

46
00:04:18,769 --> 00:04:19,870
You can come back anytime.

47
00:04:21,649 --> 00:04:22,610
But please come back.

48
00:05:06,950 --> 00:05:10,140
Mind, did you tell anyone
I came to Hua Hin?

49
00:05:10,310 --> 00:05:12,800
Uh… well…

50
00:05:13,030 --> 00:05:13,950
Well what?

51
00:05:14,690 --> 00:05:16,040
You told Pond, didn’t you?

52
00:05:16,380 --> 00:05:18,920
He called to ask me.

53
00:05:19,190 --> 00:05:22,390
He said he couldn't reach you, so I—

54
00:05:22,410 --> 00:05:23,140
So what?

55
00:05:23,890 --> 00:05:25,110
What else did you tell him?

56
00:05:26,950 --> 00:05:29,510
I only told him where
you were staying.

57
00:05:31,010 --> 00:05:34,000
Did you tell him
I've been acting strange?

58
00:05:34,990 --> 00:05:36,100
Strange how?

59
00:05:37,790 --> 00:05:39,130
Why didn't you tell him

60
00:05:39,260 --> 00:05:43,240
I am sad and withdrawn,

61
00:05:43,870 --> 00:05:44,890
like someone heartbroken?

62
00:05:45,770 --> 00:05:47,530
Are you heartbroken?

63
00:05:47,750 --> 00:05:50,670
Ugh, nothing goes my way.

64
00:05:51,420 --> 00:05:52,430
That's all.

65
00:06:03,720 --> 00:06:05,830
Hello. Are you checking in?

66
00:06:06,760 --> 00:06:09,740
Is there a guest named Donlaphat
staying here?

67
00:06:10,370 --> 00:06:11,900
That is hotel information.

68
00:06:11,930 --> 00:06:13,690
We cannot disclose it.

69
00:06:15,750 --> 00:06:18,590
Then have you seen
a small guy,

70
00:06:18,820 --> 00:06:19,890
fair-skinned,

71
00:06:19,940 --> 00:06:21,160
good-looking,

72
00:06:21,290 --> 00:06:23,520
arrogant, moody, dramatic,

73
00:06:23,590 --> 00:06:26,210
stay here in the past few days?

74
00:06:27,380 --> 00:06:28,490
I'm very sorry,

75
00:06:28,510 --> 00:06:30,690
we really can't provide that.

76
00:06:39,340 --> 00:06:40,350
Oil,

77
00:06:40,860 --> 00:06:43,370
Room 420, Mr. Donlaphat,

78
00:06:43,460 --> 00:06:45,270
reported the AC wasn't cool.

79
00:06:45,300 --> 00:06:47,180
Please have a technician check it.

80
00:06:47,370 --> 00:06:48,000
Sure.

81
00:06:48,320 --> 00:06:51,230
You can go now.
He’s walking on the beach,

82
00:06:51,250 --> 00:06:54,470
and he’ll be back once it’s fixed.

83
00:06:54,810 --> 00:06:55,820
- Okay.
- Got it.

84
00:06:57,450 --> 00:07:00,760
Must be an important guest, huh?

85
00:07:08,870 --> 00:07:09,800
All set.

86
00:07:11,490 --> 00:07:13,760
Should I send the AC technician up?

87
00:07:15,230 --> 00:07:15,940
No need.

88
00:07:16,670 --> 00:07:17,680
Actually…

89
00:07:18,300 --> 00:07:20,710
my personal technician
came from Bangkok.

90
00:07:20,900 --> 00:07:22,150
Alright.

91
00:08:06,940 --> 00:08:09,940
Mind, did Pond call?

92
00:08:10,420 --> 00:08:12,680
No, he didn’t.

93
00:08:13,710 --> 00:08:16,560
Then pretend to call him.

94
00:08:16,600 --> 00:08:19,600
Ask if he’s found me yet.

95
00:08:19,770 --> 00:08:22,270
Then find a way

96
00:08:22,980 --> 00:08:25,630
to tell him I'm walking
along the beach.

97
00:08:26,970 --> 00:08:28,930
- Is something wrong?
- Don't ask.

98
00:08:29,190 --> 00:08:29,990
That's all.

99
00:08:57,330 --> 00:08:58,720
If you're sick, see a doctor.

100
00:08:59,150 --> 00:09:00,160
Not come to the beach.

101
00:09:00,970 --> 00:09:03,720
Then why can sulky, sensitive types
come to the beach?

102
00:09:04,950 --> 00:09:05,870
Who's sulking?

103
00:09:06,000 --> 00:09:06,620
You are.

104
00:09:14,840 --> 00:09:15,450
What?

105
00:09:15,700 --> 00:09:16,710
Flowers.

106
00:09:17,600 --> 00:09:18,600
To make up.

107
00:09:25,440 --> 00:09:28,570
I had so many things to say

108
00:09:29,060 --> 00:09:30,330
but now I…

109
00:09:32,130 --> 00:09:32,850
can't get the words out.

110
00:09:38,740 --> 00:09:42,480
I'm like a kid who broke something

111
00:09:43,300 --> 00:09:44,590
and doesn't know how to apologize.

112
00:09:48,700 --> 00:09:49,950
Please take them.

113
00:09:51,340 --> 00:09:52,570
I'm here to make it up

114
00:09:53,100 --> 00:09:55,200
because I know my life without you

115
00:09:55,490 --> 00:09:57,800
is no fun, boring as hell.

116
00:10:00,770 --> 00:10:01,780
That's it?

117
00:10:02,760 --> 00:10:04,020
Actually,

118
00:10:05,430 --> 00:10:06,740
I don't want to lose you.

119
00:10:13,010 --> 00:10:17,340
Here’s your VIP client’s photographer,
new version.

120
00:10:19,310 --> 00:10:20,500
Didn't you say

121
00:10:21,480 --> 00:10:23,040
people should be themselves?

122
00:10:25,660 --> 00:10:26,670
That's right.

123
00:10:28,330 --> 00:10:30,240
But I never said we can't change.

124
00:10:32,700 --> 00:10:35,540
I may not fit into your world

125
00:10:36,130 --> 00:10:37,500
or the circles you move in.

126
00:10:40,760 --> 00:10:43,370
You know that. Why try?

127
00:10:45,900 --> 00:10:48,910
I won't give up to being unfit.

128
00:10:50,070 --> 00:10:53,860
I thought I was fine in my world.

129
00:10:55,940 --> 00:10:56,840
So good.

130
00:10:58,000 --> 00:10:58,870
Perfect.

131
00:10:59,440 --> 00:11:00,440
Elegant.

132
00:11:01,630 --> 00:11:03,190
But the day you walked in

133
00:11:04,310 --> 00:11:05,570
made me realize

134
00:11:06,880 --> 00:11:08,690
I didn't need that world anymore.

135
00:11:15,410 --> 00:11:16,900
If your world is high,

136
00:11:17,770 --> 00:11:18,870
I'll climb.

137
00:11:19,900 --> 00:11:21,740
If there are many rules,

138
00:11:22,590 --> 00:11:23,780
I'll learn.

139
00:11:24,790 --> 00:11:26,070
If it doesn't suit me,

140
00:11:26,570 --> 00:11:29,400
I'll change to stand beside you.

141
00:11:30,190 --> 00:11:31,550
But I ask one thing.

142
00:11:32,620 --> 00:11:34,430
Please don't judge me
by appearances.

143
00:11:35,300 --> 00:11:36,700
No one is judging you.

144
00:11:37,800 --> 00:11:38,940
And you,

145
00:11:39,820 --> 00:11:42,850
don't change yourself for me,
photographer.

146
00:11:44,050 --> 00:11:45,060
I want to change.

147
00:11:45,520 --> 00:11:47,510
I want you to see I'm serious.

148
00:11:48,030 --> 00:11:49,450
I want to be the one you choose

149
00:11:49,810 --> 00:11:51,420
the one who makes you happy

150
00:11:52,140 --> 00:11:53,570
not someone you overlook.

151
00:11:57,500 --> 00:11:59,670
But you look good today.

152
00:12:01,720 --> 00:12:03,070
Want to see it come off?

153
00:12:03,300 --> 00:12:04,310
Hey.

154
00:12:06,010 --> 00:12:10,250
My life can't do without
you scolding me like this.

155
00:12:11,250 --> 00:12:12,260
I missed it.

156
00:12:13,090 --> 00:12:14,620
I miss you scolding me,

157
00:12:15,130 --> 00:12:17,370
and that glare every day.

158
00:12:19,200 --> 00:12:21,660
I'm sorry I treated you badly.

159
00:12:22,010 --> 00:12:23,150
I hurt you.

160
00:12:23,820 --> 00:12:24,420
Hmm.

161
00:12:25,240 --> 00:12:26,170
Please don't be mad.

162
00:12:28,860 --> 00:12:31,320
Please, please.

163
00:12:33,710 --> 00:12:36,480
I promise, tonight I'll make it up
to you properly.

164
00:12:39,910 --> 00:12:40,910
Or maybe not?

165
00:12:43,210 --> 00:12:44,020
The full treatment.

166
00:12:45,260 --> 00:12:45,930
Sure.

167
00:12:47,380 --> 00:12:48,070
Double.

168
00:12:49,670 --> 00:12:50,380
No problem.

169
00:12:52,280 --> 00:12:54,920
Right here, right now is fine.

170
00:12:56,310 --> 00:12:57,840
Have some shame in public.

171
00:13:00,600 --> 00:13:01,800
Let's go back to how we were.

172
00:13:03,410 --> 00:13:04,270
No.

173
00:13:04,810 --> 00:13:06,230
If we come back this time,

174
00:13:06,840 --> 00:13:07,850
it has to be better.

175
00:13:08,850 --> 00:13:10,440
Yes, my wife.

176
00:13:10,580 --> 00:13:11,530
You're naughty.

177
00:13:13,150 --> 00:13:15,600
Sorry, my VIP client.

178
00:13:19,500 --> 00:13:20,510
You scruffy dog.

179
00:13:21,910 --> 00:13:23,860
My photographer.

180
00:13:28,920 --> 00:13:30,630
You've got taste too.

181
00:13:31,370 --> 00:13:32,200
Of course.

182
00:14:07,410 --> 00:14:08,340
What is this?

183
00:14:10,910 --> 00:14:12,060
Social etiquette.

184
00:14:12,810 --> 00:14:13,900
Table manners.

185
00:14:14,570 --> 00:14:16,120
Dining etiquette 101.

186
00:14:16,830 --> 00:14:19,750
Just because I can’t order wine,
choose pasta,

187
00:14:19,970 --> 00:14:21,610
and steal meat from your plate,

188
00:14:21,830 --> 00:14:23,940
I need etiquette lessons?

189
00:14:24,440 --> 00:14:25,610
It’s good to know.

190
00:14:26,210 --> 00:14:27,500
In case we attend events together.

191
00:14:28,210 --> 00:14:30,600
Okay. I won’t embarrass you,

192
00:14:31,060 --> 00:14:32,170
my VIP client.

193
00:14:40,360 --> 00:14:41,290
Whoa.

194
00:14:43,710 --> 00:14:47,110
Are we eating
or performing surgery?

195
00:14:48,380 --> 00:14:49,000
Hey.

196
00:14:51,480 --> 00:14:52,330
Sorry.

197
00:14:53,240 --> 00:14:54,030
Let’s begin.

198
00:14:54,480 --> 00:14:55,300
What first?

199
00:14:55,560 --> 00:14:57,410
Forks and knives

200
00:14:57,960 --> 00:14:59,370
aren’t chosen at random.

201
00:14:59,870 --> 00:15:01,980
Start from the outside in,

202
00:15:02,180 --> 00:15:03,170
following each course.

203
00:15:03,940 --> 00:15:07,000
If I pick wrong,
will they kick me out or whip me?

204
00:15:08,540 --> 00:15:09,470
Just your image suffers.

205
00:15:10,300 --> 00:15:13,080
And we consider image important,

206
00:15:14,150 --> 00:15:16,030
an invisible value.

207
00:15:16,550 --> 00:15:17,790
Got it.

208
00:15:19,020 --> 00:15:20,460
These are pasta types.

209
00:15:21,160 --> 00:15:23,370
Not everything is spaghetti.

210
00:15:23,760 --> 00:15:25,490
This is fettuccine,

211
00:15:25,830 --> 00:15:27,160
wide, flat, and thick.

212
00:15:27,190 --> 00:15:29,600
Linguine, oval strands.

213
00:15:29,990 --> 00:15:30,830
What’s this?

214
00:15:31,370 --> 00:15:32,090
So cute.

215
00:15:32,480 --> 00:15:33,330
Farfalle.

216
00:15:36,130 --> 00:15:37,150
And this,

217
00:15:39,270 --> 00:15:40,140
gnocchi,

218
00:15:40,860 --> 00:15:41,870
like little shells.

219
00:15:43,800 --> 00:15:45,110
And…

220
00:15:46,090 --> 00:15:47,000
capellini.

221
00:15:47,410 --> 00:15:49,250
Some call it angel hair.

222
00:15:49,850 --> 00:15:52,260
The thinnest pasta.

223
00:15:52,560 --> 00:15:53,480
Like rice noodles.

224
00:15:53,830 --> 00:15:54,400
Mm.

225
00:15:56,080 --> 00:15:58,800
Do you eat noodles often?

226
00:15:58,860 --> 00:15:59,620
Hey.

227
00:16:01,370 --> 00:16:02,340
Sorry.

228
00:16:02,960 --> 00:16:04,700
Good then.

229
00:16:05,310 --> 00:16:07,590
I’ll stop ordering spaghetti.

230
00:16:08,230 --> 00:16:09,650
Mm, good.

231
00:16:10,920 --> 00:16:13,780
White wine goes with light dishes,

232
00:16:14,220 --> 00:16:15,990
like fish or chicken.

233
00:16:17,060 --> 00:16:19,500
And red wine

234
00:16:19,690 --> 00:16:22,050
pairs with richer meats.

235
00:16:22,950 --> 00:16:25,410
This is Cabernet Sauvignon,

236
00:16:25,860 --> 00:16:28,330
the red label, and…

237
00:16:29,030 --> 00:16:29,920
Chilcas.

238
00:16:30,380 --> 00:16:31,880
This is Pinot Noir.

239
00:16:32,120 --> 00:16:32,980
Rosé.

240
00:16:34,340 --> 00:16:36,460
Champagne, sweet wines.

241
00:16:36,950 --> 00:16:39,150
Why make life this complicated

242
00:16:39,180 --> 00:16:40,180
just to eat and drink?

243
00:16:40,520 --> 00:16:42,310
It’s dining culture,

244
00:16:42,560 --> 00:16:46,060
another language we use in society.

245
00:16:46,670 --> 00:16:49,820
It saves us from explaining

246
00:16:49,840 --> 00:16:52,220
who we are and our status.

247
00:16:52,320 --> 00:16:56,080
So you do this
to have a place in your society?

248
00:16:56,500 --> 00:16:59,620
It lets us stand anywhere,
with confidence,

249
00:17:00,390 --> 00:17:01,980
and never feel beneath anyone.

250
00:17:03,190 --> 00:17:06,319
Including a place in your heart?

251
00:17:06,800 --> 00:17:08,670
You never stop teasing.

252
00:17:10,069 --> 00:17:12,270
Okay, I understand.

253
00:17:12,430 --> 00:17:14,480
- I’ll practice these.
- Mm.

254
00:17:14,500 --> 00:17:16,790
So when I stand beside you,
you won’t feel embarrassed.

255
00:17:17,140 --> 00:17:18,280
Just in case someday

256
00:17:18,609 --> 00:17:20,310
you step into my world,

257
00:17:21,170 --> 00:17:22,710
you’ll stand with confidence.

258
00:17:23,450 --> 00:17:24,569
I can do it all

259
00:17:25,270 --> 00:17:27,720
if it means you won’t feel ashamed
to have me in your life.

260
00:17:28,140 --> 00:17:31,420
My world isn’t too hard for you,
is it?

261
00:17:50,780 --> 00:17:52,200
- Thank you.
- Thank you very much.

262
00:17:52,230 --> 00:17:52,950
Thank you.

263
00:17:53,900 --> 00:17:54,790
Thank you.

264
00:18:08,550 --> 00:18:10,550
See? I told you to leave Bangkok early.

265
00:18:10,980 --> 00:18:12,870
We missed the sunset.

266
00:18:14,660 --> 00:18:16,320
It’s okay, Kin.

267
00:18:16,980 --> 00:18:20,110
Tomorrow morning we can watch
the sunrise instead.

268
00:18:20,520 --> 00:18:21,720
And if you want sunset,

269
00:18:21,930 --> 00:18:23,740
we can watch it tomorrow evening.

270
00:18:24,640 --> 00:18:27,270
But some moments,
once missed, are gone.

271
00:18:27,820 --> 00:18:30,080
We might lose certain chances.

272
00:18:32,080 --> 00:18:33,800
Not always, Kin.

273
00:18:34,340 --> 00:18:35,960
Look at the two of us.

274
00:18:36,460 --> 00:18:37,990
We missed so many things,

275
00:18:38,250 --> 00:18:39,510
but in the end,

276
00:18:39,770 --> 00:18:41,780
we still found our way back together.

277
00:18:49,370 --> 00:18:50,520
What is it?

278
00:18:51,750 --> 00:18:55,870
I’m sorry for all the things
we missed along the way.

279
00:19:01,460 --> 00:19:03,570
And this is thank you

280
00:19:04,180 --> 00:19:05,580
for never giving up.

281
00:19:11,880 --> 00:19:12,480
What?

282
00:19:13,770 --> 00:19:14,490
One more time?

283
00:19:15,170 --> 00:19:16,180
That’s enough.

284
00:19:18,670 --> 00:19:22,970
Let’s turn every mistake
into our lesson, Than.

285
00:19:23,830 --> 00:19:25,570
Yes.

286
00:19:26,600 --> 00:19:27,690
But right now,

287
00:19:28,390 --> 00:19:30,330
shouldn’t we check in first?

288
00:19:30,740 --> 00:19:33,000
Before we end up with nowhere
to sleep tonight.

289
00:19:33,170 --> 00:19:33,640
Let’s go.

290
00:19:34,950 --> 00:19:35,560
Come on.

291
00:19:36,560 --> 00:19:37,220
Kin.

292
00:19:37,330 --> 00:19:38,400
It’s beautiful.

293
00:19:38,420 --> 00:19:39,990
Does this resort feel familiar?

294
00:19:40,220 --> 00:19:41,840
Did it close for renovations?

295
00:19:41,980 --> 00:19:43,960
Why does it feel familiar?
Came with someone?

296
00:19:44,430 --> 00:19:47,750
I came alone, but last time
I met the owner, Mr. Arthit.

297
00:19:49,760 --> 00:19:50,770
How do I look?

298
00:19:51,170 --> 00:19:52,240
Is it right for tonight?

299
00:19:54,620 --> 00:19:55,860
I just bought it.

300
00:19:56,580 --> 00:19:57,590
My wallet’s empty now.

301
00:19:59,270 --> 00:20:01,170
It’s not about expensive or not.

302
00:20:01,960 --> 00:20:03,440
It’s about appropriateness,

303
00:20:03,890 --> 00:20:07,310
respecting the event
and the place,

304
00:20:07,840 --> 00:20:09,080
and it shows

305
00:20:09,100 --> 00:20:12,210
how much you value that time.

306
00:20:13,580 --> 00:20:14,830
For me,

307
00:20:16,600 --> 00:20:17,760
a moment like this

308
00:20:18,510 --> 00:20:20,050
means a lot.

309
00:20:20,810 --> 00:20:22,440
Not because of the food

310
00:20:23,280 --> 00:20:24,420
or fine wine,

311
00:20:27,560 --> 00:20:29,150
but because you are here.

312
00:20:32,030 --> 00:20:35,340
I don’t know if the changes
I’m trying to make

313
00:20:36,250 --> 00:20:37,920
will be good enough for you,

314
00:20:39,830 --> 00:20:43,290
but this photographer
will do his very best

315
00:20:44,150 --> 00:20:45,380
so I don’t lose you.

316
00:20:48,950 --> 00:20:50,060
You can speak sweetly too.

317
00:20:51,100 --> 00:20:52,490
I thought you only teased.

318
00:20:55,830 --> 00:20:59,610
Order whatever you like,
my VIP client.

319
00:21:53,960 --> 00:21:55,420
The room is beautiful, Than.

320
00:21:56,020 --> 00:21:57,500
Too bad we arrived late.

321
00:22:01,500 --> 00:22:02,210
Kin,

322
00:22:03,600 --> 00:22:06,140
the bathroom is amazing.
There’s a tub.

323
00:22:39,730 --> 00:22:40,320
What?

324
00:22:41,120 --> 00:22:43,800
That look tells me
what you’re thinking.

325
00:22:50,800 --> 00:22:52,600
With a room like this,

326
00:22:53,210 --> 00:22:54,400
it just makes me—

327
00:22:55,210 --> 00:22:56,360
That’s enough.

328
00:22:56,840 --> 00:22:59,970
That face tells me
what you’re thinking.

329
00:23:08,110 --> 00:23:10,100
Don’t you think the same?

330
00:23:18,310 --> 00:23:20,020
On this trip together,

331
00:23:20,580 --> 00:23:23,490
I think we should set some rules.

332
00:23:24,040 --> 00:23:24,580
Rules?

333
00:23:24,800 --> 00:23:25,290
Mm.

334
00:23:25,590 --> 00:23:26,730
Why rules, Than?

335
00:23:27,520 --> 00:23:28,950
To make up for things.

336
00:23:30,100 --> 00:23:31,070
Make up for what?

337
00:23:32,460 --> 00:23:34,550
For leaving me,

338
00:23:34,570 --> 00:23:36,730
making me wait for years,

339
00:23:37,070 --> 00:23:38,820
and when we met again,

340
00:23:38,850 --> 00:23:41,670
I had to chase you all over again,

341
00:23:41,700 --> 00:23:43,530
plus the thing with your friend—

342
00:23:44,050 --> 00:23:44,880
What rules?

343
00:23:45,330 --> 00:23:46,190
Let’s hear them.

344
00:23:47,390 --> 00:23:51,010
The rule is you must do
whatever I want.

345
00:23:51,410 --> 00:23:53,730
Whatever I tell you, you do it.

346
00:23:54,050 --> 00:23:58,510
And I’ll keep adding new rules
whenever I think of them.

347
00:23:58,970 --> 00:24:00,060
As many as I can.

348
00:24:01,130 --> 00:24:03,260
- And if I don’t agree?
- You don’t get to.

349
00:24:03,910 --> 00:24:07,520
You must agree
with no conditions.

350
00:24:08,110 --> 00:24:09,060
Is that so?

351
00:24:12,590 --> 00:24:15,010
Don’t talk back to me, got it?

352
00:24:15,820 --> 00:24:17,530
You’re really pushing it now.

353
00:24:19,590 --> 00:24:21,200
Rule number one:

354
00:24:22,250 --> 00:24:24,190
you must call me something new.

355
00:24:24,710 --> 00:24:25,610
Something new?

356
00:24:25,830 --> 00:24:28,380
I’ll let you choose what to call me.

357
00:24:32,260 --> 00:24:33,110
Bii.

358
00:24:34,210 --> 00:24:34,940
Bii.

359
00:24:35,420 --> 00:24:36,710
From “baby.”

360
00:24:38,230 --> 00:24:40,200
No, that doesn’t suit me.

361
00:24:40,890 --> 00:24:41,590
Babe?

362
00:24:44,110 --> 00:24:44,710
No.

363
00:24:45,680 --> 00:24:46,440
Darling?

364
00:24:47,130 --> 00:24:49,770
- No, no.
- No, no?

365
00:24:53,390 --> 00:24:54,480
Honey?

366
00:24:55,690 --> 00:24:56,460
No.

367
00:24:56,480 --> 00:24:58,030
Honey, honey?

368
00:24:58,060 --> 00:24:59,490
No, Than, that’s embarrassing.

369
00:24:59,520 --> 00:25:00,570
Good boy?

370
00:25:02,930 --> 00:25:04,200
Hubby?

371
00:25:04,470 --> 00:25:05,320
Than.

372
00:25:06,470 --> 00:25:10,420
Ugh, I can’t think anymore.
You won’t choose anything?

373
00:25:13,130 --> 00:25:13,900
Then

374
00:25:15,150 --> 00:25:17,100
use everything I just said.

375
00:25:17,480 --> 00:25:21,340
Switch them around.
I’ll decide which I like.

376
00:25:21,930 --> 00:25:24,340
So what should I start with?

377
00:25:25,370 --> 00:25:26,900
Start with

378
00:25:29,060 --> 00:25:30,350
baby.

379
00:25:32,780 --> 00:25:34,940
Alright, baby.

380
00:25:41,340 --> 00:25:44,590
Kiss my cheek. Don’t hesitate.

381
00:25:46,740 --> 00:25:47,480
Double.

382
00:25:53,660 --> 00:25:57,060
You go change first.

383
00:25:57,690 --> 00:26:00,770
I have dinner surprise ready.

384
00:26:01,550 --> 00:26:02,380
Another surprise?

385
00:26:03,060 --> 00:26:04,670
Not telling.

386
00:26:07,400 --> 00:26:08,400
So many surprises.

387
00:26:08,680 --> 00:26:10,570
What, you don’t like them?

388
00:26:10,680 --> 00:26:12,300
I like them, baby.

389
00:26:12,500 --> 00:26:13,610
What was that?

390
00:26:13,670 --> 00:26:15,800
I like them, baby.

391
00:26:16,120 --> 00:26:17,290
Baby.

392
00:26:18,330 --> 00:26:19,210
That’s enough.

393
00:26:22,660 --> 00:26:23,760
This bottle is like you.

394
00:26:25,310 --> 00:26:25,990
How?

395
00:26:27,690 --> 00:26:29,830
A beautiful aroma, deep,

396
00:26:30,700 --> 00:26:32,120
intriguing.

397
00:26:33,610 --> 00:26:34,950
But the label tells me…

398
00:26:36,470 --> 00:26:37,210
expensive,

399
00:26:38,170 --> 00:26:39,100
hard to reach.

400
00:26:41,700 --> 00:26:43,610
But once you taste it,

401
00:26:44,640 --> 00:26:46,000
you want to keep sipping,

402
00:26:46,710 --> 00:26:47,720
sip until you’re drunk.

403
00:26:49,210 --> 00:26:50,430
Good wine

404
00:26:51,680 --> 00:26:52,800
doesn’t rush.

405
00:26:53,930 --> 00:26:56,710
It should be savored slowly,

406
00:26:57,370 --> 00:26:58,380
tasted gently,

407
00:27:01,110 --> 00:27:02,550
learned gradually.

408
00:27:05,020 --> 00:27:06,140
But this one’s good,

409
00:27:07,690 --> 00:27:09,170
great aroma and body.

410
00:27:11,700 --> 00:27:12,530
This one’s nice too.

411
00:27:13,540 --> 00:27:14,550
From France.

412
00:27:18,590 --> 00:27:21,260
If I try them all tonight,

413
00:27:22,250 --> 00:27:22,830
I’ll fall asleep.

414
00:27:24,100 --> 00:27:25,220
Who said you could sleep?

415
00:27:26,500 --> 00:27:27,130
Hey—

416
00:27:28,370 --> 00:27:29,570
you said that yourself.

417
00:27:31,410 --> 00:27:35,000
Sometimes I can’t read you.

418
00:27:36,150 --> 00:27:37,910
Sometimes you seem fiery,

419
00:27:38,490 --> 00:27:40,130
sometimes cold.

420
00:27:41,800 --> 00:27:42,720
Do you like that?

421
00:27:44,290 --> 00:27:44,910
Very much.

422
00:27:45,600 --> 00:27:46,650
It’s intriguing.

423
00:27:47,870 --> 00:27:49,570
Tonight,

424
00:27:50,740 --> 00:27:52,410
I have more for you to discover.

425
00:27:55,230 --> 00:27:57,530
We’ve covered table manners.

426
00:27:59,550 --> 00:28:01,060
What about bed manners?

427
00:28:09,670 --> 00:28:10,920
Just as important.

428
00:28:11,560 --> 00:28:13,220
Because in bed,

429
00:28:13,840 --> 00:28:16,240
it’s not about showing skill,

430
00:28:16,900 --> 00:28:19,430
but how much you value it.

431
00:28:21,080 --> 00:28:22,380
When to be quick,

432
00:28:23,220 --> 00:28:24,600
when to slow down,

433
00:28:25,940 --> 00:28:27,280
and most importantly,

434
00:28:28,920 --> 00:28:32,790
you must listen to your partner’s body.

435
00:28:35,450 --> 00:28:36,980
Now that’s interesting.

436
00:28:38,490 --> 00:28:39,500
Shall we go?

437
00:28:40,630 --> 00:28:41,880
Waiting

438
00:28:42,940 --> 00:28:44,390
is a kind of etiquette.

439
00:28:44,930 --> 00:28:47,620
What we wait for has charm,

440
00:28:52,490 --> 00:28:54,840
especially what we desire most.

441
00:29:18,170 --> 00:29:19,850
How is it, darling?

442
00:29:20,140 --> 00:29:23,060
A surprise squid boat dinner.

443
00:29:24,410 --> 00:29:25,570
I can’t, Kin.

444
00:29:25,980 --> 00:29:28,120
The boat keeps rocking.

445
00:29:28,600 --> 00:29:29,570
I surrender.

446
00:29:31,430 --> 00:29:32,380
No more, okay?

447
00:29:32,760 --> 00:29:34,020
No more.

448
00:29:39,510 --> 00:29:40,360
This way, please.

449
00:29:40,980 --> 00:29:41,690
Fresh squid.

450
00:29:42,300 --> 00:29:42,910
Thank you.

451
00:29:44,600 --> 00:29:45,380
- Thank you.
- Okay.

452
00:29:48,400 --> 00:29:50,740
Let’s switch from the boat
to here instead.

453
00:29:54,550 --> 00:29:56,680
There’s squid sashimi you like.

454
00:29:59,100 --> 00:29:59,800
Who?

455
00:30:00,960 --> 00:30:02,110
Your favorite.

456
00:30:03,860 --> 00:30:04,520
What?

457
00:30:05,270 --> 00:30:06,730
- Huh?
- Who?

458
00:30:08,190 --> 00:30:09,480
Oh.

459
00:30:11,100 --> 00:30:15,260
Here you go, babe — fresh squid
with spicy dipping sauce.

460
00:30:16,180 --> 00:30:17,590
Spicy will cure seasickness.

461
00:30:22,280 --> 00:30:23,460
You’ve got sauce on your lips.

462
00:30:31,440 --> 00:30:33,320
How is it? Good?

463
00:30:33,700 --> 00:30:34,320
Good.

464
00:30:35,060 --> 00:30:35,880
So spicy.

465
00:30:37,470 --> 00:30:38,000
Here.

466
00:30:41,000 --> 00:30:42,910
- Say ah.
- I can feed myself.

467
00:30:43,500 --> 00:30:44,630
Resisting?

468
00:30:45,250 --> 00:30:49,170
Don’t forget the rule.
You must do what I want.

469
00:30:51,340 --> 00:30:54,140
- I want to feed you.
- Okay.

470
00:30:54,460 --> 00:30:56,570
Say ah…

471
00:31:00,550 --> 00:31:02,490
That’s adorable.

472
00:31:03,000 --> 00:31:05,070
You’re cute when you’re obedient.

473
00:31:08,250 --> 00:31:10,310
Tomorrow morning, let’s jog

474
00:31:10,680 --> 00:31:12,580
and watch the sunrise.

475
00:31:13,960 --> 00:31:14,550
Sure.

476
00:31:14,900 --> 00:31:15,950
Not so blunt.

477
00:31:17,010 --> 00:31:18,650
You should say,

478
00:31:19,180 --> 00:31:20,320
“Yes,

479
00:31:21,210 --> 00:31:21,970
hubby."

480
00:31:22,220 --> 00:31:23,860
Than, no.

481
00:31:24,560 --> 00:31:25,570
Ah-ah.

482
00:31:26,560 --> 00:31:29,030
Break the rule, get punished.

483
00:31:29,440 --> 00:31:31,340
Say "hubby" first.

484
00:31:31,780 --> 00:31:32,790
No, I won’t.

485
00:31:33,510 --> 00:31:35,370
Come on, hurry.

486
00:31:36,290 --> 00:31:39,990
Tomorrow morning
we jog together, honey.

487
00:31:40,500 --> 00:31:41,690
Jogging, okay?

488
00:31:42,180 --> 00:31:43,180
But I won’t say it.

489
00:31:46,850 --> 00:31:49,270
So you won’t say "hubby?"

490
00:31:51,670 --> 00:31:52,330
Fine.

491
00:31:53,380 --> 00:31:55,470
Then you deserve punishment.

492
00:31:57,090 --> 00:31:59,300
Let’s see what it will be.

493
00:32:00,660 --> 00:32:02,610
Ouch, hubby—

494
00:32:02,840 --> 00:32:04,250
That’s enough, Than. Stop.

495
00:32:04,480 --> 00:32:06,690
What did I tell you to call me?

496
00:32:07,350 --> 00:32:09,360
Hubby— ouch!

497
00:32:10,880 --> 00:32:12,880
- That hurts, Than.
- Still not say it?

498
00:32:14,320 --> 00:32:16,210
Ouch… I can’t take it.

499
00:32:17,010 --> 00:32:18,770
Take it out— ouch!

500
00:32:19,370 --> 00:32:22,330
- Than, I really can’t.
- Not yet.

501
00:32:22,910 --> 00:32:23,950
Wait, wait.

502
00:32:24,230 --> 00:32:25,690
- Not yet.
- Let me rest.

503
00:32:26,330 --> 00:32:27,070
Say it.

504
00:32:27,520 --> 00:32:28,420
Hubby.

505
00:32:29,370 --> 00:32:30,750
Ah, that hurts.

506
00:32:31,670 --> 00:32:33,440
That’s it, naughty boy.

507
00:32:34,080 --> 00:32:36,210
Now you know what happens.

508
00:32:39,170 --> 00:32:40,420
Come here.

509
00:32:40,960 --> 00:32:43,640
Ouch— take it out, dear.

510
00:32:44,310 --> 00:32:44,980
It hurts.

511
00:32:45,560 --> 00:32:46,560
Spell it.

512
00:32:47,280 --> 00:32:50,190
Spell it properly
so you won’t be shy later

513
00:32:50,520 --> 00:32:52,970
when you call me hubby.

514
00:32:53,490 --> 00:32:54,650
Hubby.

515
00:32:55,900 --> 00:32:56,910
- Take it out.
- Let me hear.

516
00:32:57,040 --> 00:32:59,300
Say it again, sweetly.
I want it sweet.

517
00:32:59,830 --> 00:33:01,130
Hubby.

518
00:33:02,310 --> 00:33:03,610
- Please.
- Again.

519
00:33:04,270 --> 00:33:05,360
Hubby.

520
00:33:21,530 --> 00:33:22,650
Will you say it now?

521
00:33:23,220 --> 00:33:24,570
I said it.

522
00:33:24,590 --> 00:33:26,650
- Say what?
- Hubby.

523
00:33:27,060 --> 00:33:28,090
Take it out, please.

524
00:33:29,450 --> 00:33:30,520
Can I put it back?

525
00:33:36,070 --> 00:33:37,180
Hubby dear.

526
00:33:38,060 --> 00:33:38,910
What was that?

527
00:33:56,290 --> 00:33:57,810
I want you to experience

528
00:33:58,740 --> 00:34:00,470
my style of bed artistry.

529
00:34:02,470 --> 00:34:03,720
And before this?

530
00:34:04,240 --> 00:34:05,190
It wasn’t bad.

531
00:34:07,060 --> 00:34:08,449
But tonight,

532
00:34:11,580 --> 00:34:13,780
I want you to open yourself

533
00:34:14,840 --> 00:34:16,210
and try something new.

534
00:34:17,380 --> 00:34:18,139
Of course,

535
00:34:19,020 --> 00:34:20,290
my VIP client.

536
00:34:24,290 --> 00:34:26,790
Easy now, photographer.

537
00:34:30,429 --> 00:34:32,080
Tonight is my game.

538
00:35:22,770 --> 00:35:23,970
Not too hard, right?

539
00:36:01,970 --> 00:36:03,010
You learn quickly.

540
00:36:51,770 --> 00:36:52,400
Hey—

541
00:36:53,970 --> 00:36:55,930
this isn’t the time to rush.

542
00:36:57,150 --> 00:36:59,400
You need to learn gentle touch,

543
00:37:00,530 --> 00:37:01,360
unhurried,

544
00:37:02,370 --> 00:37:03,360
slow.

545
00:37:08,210 --> 00:37:08,860
Yes.

546
00:37:10,150 --> 00:37:12,360
Like this, my client?

547
00:37:24,470 --> 00:37:26,170
Another lesson to learn:

548
00:37:29,020 --> 00:37:31,050
in a world that speaks of equality—

549
00:37:33,080 --> 00:37:33,890
what is it?

550
00:37:39,460 --> 00:37:43,610
After being a good giver,
try being a receiver.

551
00:37:45,550 --> 00:37:46,640
No, no.

552
00:37:47,540 --> 00:37:49,200
Getting bold, aren’t you,
proud cat?

553
00:37:52,130 --> 00:37:53,280
I’ll handle it.

554
00:38:51,190 --> 00:38:51,810
Than.

555
00:38:59,300 --> 00:39:02,620
Waking up to morning ozone like this

556
00:39:02,710 --> 00:39:05,180
feels refreshing, right, Kin?

557
00:39:05,470 --> 00:39:06,040
True.

558
00:39:07,000 --> 00:39:09,110
Letting your lungs breathe fresh air

559
00:39:09,670 --> 00:39:11,350
is way better than Bangkok.

560
00:39:13,320 --> 00:39:14,500
- Follow me.
- Hm?

561
00:39:17,690 --> 00:39:18,890
Inner energy training?

562
00:39:19,490 --> 00:39:21,400
Breathing in fresh air.

563
00:39:21,550 --> 00:39:22,380
Oh.

564
00:39:32,430 --> 00:39:34,820
First mission of the day.

565
00:39:35,600 --> 00:39:36,770
What mission now?

566
00:39:38,540 --> 00:39:41,000
Selfies as ordered by Than.

567
00:39:41,600 --> 00:39:42,550
Sounds difficult.

568
00:39:42,830 --> 00:39:44,400
Not at all, it’s easy.

569
00:39:44,420 --> 00:39:47,980
Just pose how I tell you.

570
00:39:48,760 --> 00:39:50,920
I won’t tease you, darling.

571
00:39:51,600 --> 00:39:55,280
So what pose do you want?

572
00:39:59,330 --> 00:40:01,060
First pose:

573
00:40:02,640 --> 00:40:06,930
smile like you’re thrilled
to have a puppy-type boyfriend.

574
00:40:07,790 --> 00:40:09,070
- Puppy?
- Puppy.

575
00:40:09,090 --> 00:40:11,000
- How?
- Try it.

576
00:40:14,450 --> 00:40:15,270
Smile.

577
00:40:15,580 --> 00:40:17,720
- Hey, be happy.
- Oh, happy?

578
00:40:18,860 --> 00:40:20,560
- Doggy ears.
- Doggy ears.

579
00:40:24,740 --> 00:40:26,040
Okay, woof woof.

580
00:40:26,250 --> 00:40:26,950
Woof woof.

581
00:40:28,980 --> 00:40:31,790
Next pose:

582
00:40:33,320 --> 00:40:34,220
eating spicy food

583
00:40:35,310 --> 00:40:37,290
until it burns.

584
00:40:38,740 --> 00:40:39,840
One…

585
00:40:42,470 --> 00:40:44,540
Spicier! More zing!

586
00:40:45,260 --> 00:40:46,790
- More zing.
- That’s enough.

587
00:40:47,790 --> 00:40:50,790
- Do a cheek kiss.
- Cheek kiss.

588
00:40:52,420 --> 00:40:53,060
Mwah.

589
00:40:54,640 --> 00:40:55,920
Cross your eyes, pout.

590
00:41:01,780 --> 00:41:04,740
Last pose:

591
00:41:06,310 --> 00:41:07,950
kind Kin

592
00:41:09,380 --> 00:41:11,330
who never stops loving Than.

593
00:41:24,630 --> 00:41:26,020
Show the ring, show it.

594
00:41:26,840 --> 00:41:28,910
Honeymoon time— don’t block my face.

595
00:41:29,320 --> 00:41:31,340
Honeymoon time!

596
00:41:33,920 --> 00:41:35,460
- Woof. Woof.
- Woof woof.

597
00:41:46,370 --> 00:41:47,370
Darling.

598
00:41:50,600 --> 00:41:51,930
Darling.

599
00:41:54,710 --> 00:41:55,760
Darling.

600
00:41:58,440 --> 00:41:59,440
Who are you calling darling?

601
00:42:00,110 --> 00:42:01,650
I’m calling you darling.

602
00:42:01,680 --> 00:42:02,750
Don’t call me darling

603
00:42:03,190 --> 00:42:04,690
if you don’t mean it.

604
00:42:05,600 --> 00:42:07,110
I do love you.

605
00:42:09,040 --> 00:42:11,660
Wait a sec, I need your opinion.

606
00:42:30,480 --> 00:42:31,490
Hey—

607
00:42:32,580 --> 00:42:33,380
are you okay?

608
00:42:33,870 --> 00:42:34,490
Why?

609
00:42:35,440 --> 00:42:38,780
Donlaphat version… like this,
you don’t like it?

610
00:42:39,900 --> 00:42:40,290
Well…

611
00:42:41,620 --> 00:42:42,760
It looks different.

612
00:42:46,210 --> 00:42:48,640
So it’s not right yet.

613
00:42:49,590 --> 00:42:50,230
Then…

614
00:42:51,170 --> 00:42:52,220
wait a second.

615
00:42:54,750 --> 00:42:57,280
How about this one?
Can you handle it?

616
00:43:00,430 --> 00:43:01,000
This one?

617
00:43:16,530 --> 00:43:19,100
This one works.

618
00:43:27,590 --> 00:43:30,500
What got into you? Changing styles?

619
00:43:30,830 --> 00:43:31,360
Why?

620
00:43:32,350 --> 00:43:34,420
Yesterday you tried to change for me.

621
00:43:35,460 --> 00:43:36,980
Why can’t I change for you?

622
00:43:37,740 --> 00:43:40,020
You’re good just the way you are.

623
00:43:41,180 --> 00:43:42,300
That’s the real you.

624
00:43:44,570 --> 00:43:46,130
And the way you were yesterday—

625
00:43:47,080 --> 00:43:48,240
was that the real you?

626
00:43:55,560 --> 00:43:56,870
I’m fine with anything.

627
00:43:57,750 --> 00:43:58,820
I can be anything,

628
00:44:00,180 --> 00:44:01,500
as long as you’re with me.

629
00:44:02,770 --> 00:44:05,840
Suit and tie, tuxedo,

630
00:44:06,510 --> 00:44:09,430
designer clothes, fine dining,

631
00:44:10,110 --> 00:44:11,220
a glamorous life—

632
00:44:11,990 --> 00:44:12,690
I can do it all.

633
00:44:15,440 --> 00:44:16,270
Thank you.

634
00:44:18,640 --> 00:44:20,000
But wouldn’t it be better

635
00:44:20,810 --> 00:44:22,250
if we stayed ourselves,

636
00:44:23,140 --> 00:44:24,330
the way we’ve always been,

637
00:44:25,050 --> 00:44:28,110
respecting each other’s space,

638
00:44:28,690 --> 00:44:31,030
living in each other’s worlds
without discomfort?

639
00:44:38,030 --> 00:44:39,430
Two people

640
00:44:40,790 --> 00:44:43,550
don’t have to be the same
to be together.

641
00:44:44,670 --> 00:44:45,790
Differences

642
00:44:46,120 --> 00:44:47,830
help us learn

643
00:44:48,780 --> 00:44:50,260
and complete each other.

644
00:44:52,290 --> 00:44:54,410
Wouldn’t that be better, photographer?

645
00:44:56,480 --> 00:44:58,330
Thank you, my client,

646
00:44:59,880 --> 00:45:01,080
for understanding me

647
00:45:02,080 --> 00:45:03,070
and who I am.

648
00:45:05,730 --> 00:45:06,760
Thank you too,

649
00:45:08,130 --> 00:45:08,980
you scruffy dog.

650
00:45:13,690 --> 00:45:16,830
How about one more
this morning?

651
00:45:18,090 --> 00:45:19,100
Don’t rush.

652
00:45:20,290 --> 00:45:21,610
The art of waiting.

653
00:45:22,520 --> 00:45:23,310
Alright.

654
00:45:24,350 --> 00:45:26,290
Then tonight,

655
00:45:27,330 --> 00:45:29,510
let’s see what I prepare
to broaden your world.

656
00:45:31,290 --> 00:45:32,150
I’m not afraid.

657
00:45:34,640 --> 00:45:37,440
Go shower. We’ll get breakfast.

658
00:45:40,250 --> 00:45:41,420
Breakfast here is great.

659
00:45:44,950 --> 00:45:45,710
Go shower.

660
00:45:51,350 --> 00:45:52,070
Hey—

661
00:45:53,420 --> 00:45:53,940
Go.

662
00:45:57,750 --> 00:45:58,600
Is it okay?

663
00:45:58,790 --> 00:46:00,170
- How is it?
- Excellent.

664
00:46:00,610 --> 00:46:03,850
But first, let me take Inozyme.

665
00:46:04,560 --> 00:46:06,760
It helps with digestion

666
00:46:08,480 --> 00:46:10,770
and makes my stomach feel better.

667
00:46:11,350 --> 00:46:13,030
I told you not to eat so much.

668
00:46:13,160 --> 00:46:14,470
Who was I with?

669
00:46:21,980 --> 00:46:23,150
Drink some water too.

670
00:46:29,390 --> 00:46:31,780
All set, ready to go.

671
00:46:32,480 --> 00:46:36,610
Now I’ll present today’s
special menu to you.

672
00:46:36,640 --> 00:46:37,670
Yes, my lord.

673
00:46:37,880 --> 00:46:38,550
Here.

674
00:46:40,040 --> 00:46:42,440
Aromatic Bang Khla coconut water,

675
00:46:43,280 --> 00:46:45,820
refreshing and hydrating.

676
00:46:45,910 --> 00:46:50,240
Between this coconut
and my cheek, which smells better?

677
00:46:50,520 --> 00:46:51,410
May I smell first?

678
00:46:52,170 --> 00:46:53,350
Alright, moving on.

679
00:46:53,560 --> 00:46:56,360
Next, Tha Uthen pineapple,

680
00:46:56,800 --> 00:46:58,590
sweet for sure.

681
00:46:59,290 --> 00:47:00,900
Guaranteed sweetness.

682
00:47:01,830 --> 00:47:05,020
We also have Nong Hiang jackfruit,

683
00:47:05,100 --> 00:47:08,380
and to finish, Koh Sukorn watermelon.

684
00:47:11,640 --> 00:47:13,610
- Which first?
- They all look good.

685
00:47:15,000 --> 00:47:15,790
This one.

686
00:47:18,690 --> 00:47:20,140
Say ah—

687
00:47:20,990 --> 00:47:23,610
No, my lord. Too many people.

688
00:47:24,720 --> 00:47:25,470
I’ll eat it myself.

689
00:47:25,720 --> 00:47:28,140
Hey, today you’re the servant.

690
00:47:28,220 --> 00:47:30,450
You must obey your lord.

691
00:47:30,980 --> 00:47:32,780
Come on, ah—

692
00:47:33,100 --> 00:47:35,600
- Yes, yes.
- Ah—

693
00:47:37,580 --> 00:47:40,510
See? Nothing to be shy about.

694
00:47:41,110 --> 00:47:43,200
We’re married now.

695
00:47:43,300 --> 00:47:47,120
We should show the world
how much we love each other,

696
00:47:47,140 --> 00:47:48,150
right, baby?

697
00:47:49,080 --> 00:47:50,050
Right, honey?

698
00:47:54,370 --> 00:47:56,860
Do you love me, my servant?

699
00:47:59,010 --> 00:48:00,740
You’re pushing it now.

700
00:48:01,800 --> 00:48:04,120
Careful, you might get payback.

701
00:48:05,260 --> 00:48:06,980
Come on, one more bite.

702
00:48:07,140 --> 00:48:09,190
This time, jackfruit.

703
00:48:09,600 --> 00:48:10,850
What, already full?

704
00:48:11,660 --> 00:48:14,700
You can still eat. Ah—

705
00:48:18,020 --> 00:48:20,720
- My loyal servant.
- Tan, Mr. Don and Pond—

706
00:48:20,960 --> 00:48:22,670
That’s Akin and Than.

707
00:48:22,890 --> 00:48:25,500
Then let’s pretend
we just met here.

708
00:48:29,110 --> 00:48:30,140
Hello, Mr. Don.

709
00:48:31,440 --> 00:48:32,450
Mr. Tan, Mr. Akin.

710
00:48:33,350 --> 00:48:33,930
Pond.

711
00:48:35,690 --> 00:48:36,390
Oh—

712
00:48:37,060 --> 00:48:38,630
Bro, Mr. Don.

713
00:48:39,210 --> 00:48:42,010
You two just happened
to meet here, right?

714
00:48:42,400 --> 00:48:45,860
Hua Hin is huge,

715
00:48:45,940 --> 00:48:47,400
yet you still ran into each other.

716
00:48:48,060 --> 00:48:49,360
- Perfect timing.
- No.

717
00:48:49,590 --> 00:48:51,640
We actually came together.

718
00:48:57,290 --> 00:48:58,000
And

719
00:48:58,640 --> 00:48:59,860
we’re dating.

720
00:49:10,350 --> 00:49:12,150
Pond is a nice guy,

721
00:49:12,210 --> 00:49:14,010
even if he looks a bit scary—

722
00:49:14,030 --> 00:49:15,040
- but he—
- Than.

723
00:49:15,800 --> 00:49:16,820
He’s a good man.

724
00:49:17,100 --> 00:49:19,690
I know. If he weren’t…

725
00:49:20,370 --> 00:49:21,800
I wouldn’t go public.

726
00:49:25,120 --> 00:49:28,250
Alright then, we won’t disturb you.

727
00:49:28,590 --> 00:49:30,290
We’ll excuse ourselves—

728
00:49:32,420 --> 00:49:33,920
May we sit over there?

729
00:49:36,670 --> 00:49:38,100
Of course. Please.

730
00:49:39,940 --> 00:49:42,060
Please, Pond.
Please, Mr. Don.

731
00:49:45,340 --> 00:49:47,240
Nice running into you here.

732
00:49:47,500 --> 00:49:48,940
Have you ordered yet?

733
00:49:49,200 --> 00:49:49,900
Yes.

734
00:49:50,180 --> 00:49:51,040
Try it.

735
00:49:51,170 --> 00:49:52,710
- Oh, perfect timing.
- Thank you.

736
00:49:53,550 --> 00:49:54,550
Thank you.

737
00:50:00,560 --> 00:50:02,300
Would you like sauce?
I can pour it.

738
00:50:02,330 --> 00:50:04,590
It’s fine. Let Pond do it.

739
00:50:09,040 --> 00:50:10,230
Have some sauce.

740
00:50:10,380 --> 00:50:11,620
- Chili sauce.
- I’ll feed you.

741
00:50:11,650 --> 00:50:12,600
Okay.

742
00:50:14,660 --> 00:50:15,700
I’ll do it.

743
00:50:16,040 --> 00:50:17,400
Where’s this pineapple from?

744
00:50:17,550 --> 00:50:19,020
From Tha Uthen.

745
00:50:19,050 --> 00:50:19,890
- Oh.
- Yes.

746
00:50:19,910 --> 00:50:21,440
They say it’s very sweet.

747
00:50:21,470 --> 00:50:22,510
A famous local specialty.

748
00:50:22,960 --> 00:50:23,930
Alright then—

749
00:50:23,950 --> 00:50:26,820
- I’ll scoop some.
- Let Mr. Don eat more, Pond.

750
00:50:27,910 --> 00:50:30,980
I think Pond should eat more.

751
00:50:32,700 --> 00:50:33,970
The right one.

752
00:50:34,000 --> 00:50:35,250
Then go ahead and eat.

753
00:50:36,700 --> 00:50:38,060
Can I gossip about him?

754
00:50:38,090 --> 00:50:38,790
About what?

755
00:50:44,820 --> 00:50:47,520
No matter how many times
we start over,

756
00:50:48,250 --> 00:50:49,750
it’s always this person.

757
00:50:50,840 --> 00:50:52,030
Same for me.

758
00:50:52,900 --> 00:50:54,370
We’re lucky

759
00:50:54,400 --> 00:50:56,380
to begin again together.

760
00:50:58,600 --> 00:51:00,070
I have to thank Kin

761
00:51:00,490 --> 00:51:03,160
for giving me another chance
to prove myself.

762
00:51:03,870 --> 00:51:05,570
I should thank you too

763
00:51:06,140 --> 00:51:08,660
for staying strong
and never changing.

764
00:51:13,370 --> 00:51:14,570
We’re being interviewed.

765
00:51:17,410 --> 00:51:20,320
He always loses to puppy types.

766
00:51:25,550 --> 00:51:26,130
Hey—

767
00:51:27,350 --> 00:51:28,780
We’re different in almost everything,

768
00:51:29,610 --> 00:51:31,360
but he taught me

769
00:51:32,320 --> 00:51:33,620
that differences aren’t a problem

770
00:51:34,870 --> 00:51:38,630
when you open your heart
and begin again with someone.

771
00:51:40,550 --> 00:51:42,170
Love isn’t about changing anyone;

772
00:51:42,740 --> 00:51:45,110
it’s about opening your heart

773
00:51:46,430 --> 00:51:48,190
and starting again as yourself.

774
00:51:51,200 --> 00:51:54,410
I’m sorry I can’t be
the perfect man.

775
00:51:55,940 --> 00:51:57,570
I don’t want perfect.

776
00:51:58,260 --> 00:51:59,270
I want you,

777
00:51:59,950 --> 00:52:00,790
you photographer.

778
00:52:02,240 --> 00:52:03,160
Give me a kiss.

779
00:52:03,390 --> 00:52:04,160
No.

780
00:52:05,960 --> 00:52:07,230
- Come on.
- No.

781
00:53:00,620 --> 00:53:02,130
This bucket liquor is strange.

782
00:53:03,410 --> 00:53:04,950
Didn’t expect it to taste this good.

783
00:53:07,000 --> 00:53:09,420
It’s not a premium drink
like you’re used to,

784
00:53:09,750 --> 00:53:11,160
no fancy name,

785
00:53:12,280 --> 00:53:13,160
no vintage year,

786
00:53:14,100 --> 00:53:15,450
no fixed recipe,

787
00:53:16,400 --> 00:53:17,670
but it feels comforting.

788
00:53:20,650 --> 00:53:21,470
Thank you

789
00:53:22,540 --> 00:53:24,480
for taking me out
of my comfort zone.

790
00:53:25,060 --> 00:53:26,970
I’ll take you even further.

791
00:53:29,420 --> 00:53:30,090
How?

792
00:53:32,510 --> 00:53:35,780
Have you ever tried a B-56?

793
00:53:38,440 --> 00:53:42,470
I only know the B-52.

794
00:53:44,400 --> 00:53:46,190
Then try the B-56.

795
00:53:46,710 --> 00:53:47,810
You’ll get hooked.
